definition.value: A 3-oxo-5beta-steroid that is 5beta-cholestan-3-one bearing two additional hydroxy substituents at positions 7alpha and 12alpha.

A member of the class of indazoles that is 1H-indazole substituted by a [6-(methylamino)-3-nitropyridin-2-yl]amino group at position 5. It is an inhibitor of heat shock factor 1 (IC50 = 1.2muM) and suppresses tumour growth in mouse xenograft models.
Any inhibitor that interferes with the action of heat shock factor 1.
An ammonium ion derivative resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen atom of a primary methyl amino compound. Major species at pH 7.3.
Epinephrine Bitartrate is the bitartrate salt form of epinephrine, a direct-acting sympathomimetic amine with bronchodilator and vasoconstricting activity.
An organosulfonate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 3-(trimethylsilyl)propane-1-sulfonic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the sulfo group; Major species at pH 7.3.
